<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53047z"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53047z">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53047z"> 47(z)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> I intended to study = I was 15 / (lian ku) <small>Green</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53047z"><li>FW 89.29 </li><li><a href="../../flex/d/lexd.htm#n53047z">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/d/l39d.htm#n53047z">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53047z">MS BL 47476a-196</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:413 <a name="dd10" href="../../ff/fdra/dda.htm#dd10">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/d/dd10.htm#n53047z">Draft: I.4&sect;1.10</a>/2.10 </li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: In the <i>Lun y&uuml;</i>, or Confucian discourses (first book, second chapter, fourth paragraph), one reads &ldquo;At fifteen I was intend upon learning, at thirty I was composed (<i>san shi er li</i>: thirty then stand)&rdquo;. An educated Chinaman would, by saying &ldquo;I intended to study&rdquo;, indicate that he has been fifteen at the time in question. </mm> </dd></dl>
